cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about multilingual neural machine translation (MNMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses various modeling principles and challenges, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). MNMT involves training neural networks, which falls under the scope of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of distributed representations, which is a common technique in computer vision (CV), indicating that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
